This file previously contained the old KVM_CAP_NESTED_VMBUS_RELAY patch
(private sentinel 0x4f564d52). It has been superseded.

The current relay uses KVM_CAP_NESTED_HYPERV_HCALL_RELAY (cap 249, the upstream
RFC number) with a bitmask args[0] selecting the relayable hypercall classes.

**Source of truth for the Proxmox VE kernel variant:**
  build/kvm_patch_apply_hcall_relay.sh
  (anchored text insertions; apply to a kernel source tree matching `uname -r`)

**Upstream RFC form (mainline kernel):**
  github.com/bitranox/linux-nested-vmbus-relay, branch nested-vmbus-relay
  Two patches: (1) rename nested_evmcs_l2_tlb_flush_enabled to
  nested_evmcs_l2_direct_hypercall_enabled, (2) add the relay.
